### 6. **UIToolInvocation State Transitions**

Tool invocations in `responseMessage.parts` progress through states:

```typescript
type UIToolInvocation<TOOL> = {
  toolCallId: string;
  title?: string;
  providerExecuted?: boolean;
} & (
  // Input is being streamed in
  | {
      state: 'input-streaming';
      input: DeepPartial<TOOL['input']> | undefined;
      output?: never;
      errorText?: never;
      callProviderMetadata?: ProviderMetadata;
    }
  // Input is complete, ready to execute
  | {
      state: 'input-available';
      input: TOOL['input'];
      output?: never;
      errorText?: never;
      callProviderMetadata?: ProviderMetadata;
    }
  // Tool execution completed successfully
  | {
      state: 'output-available';
      input: TOOL['input'];
      output: TOOL['output'];
      errorText?: never;
      callProviderMetadata?: ProviderMetadata;
      preliminary?: boolean; // Not yet finalized
    }
  // Tool execution failed
  | {
      state: 'output-error';
      input: TOOL['input'] | undefined;
      rawInput?: unknown;
      output?: never;
      errorText: string;
      callProviderMetadata?: ProviderMetadata;
    }
  // Tool call was denied (approval-required tool rejected)
  | {
      state: 'output-denied';
      input: TOOL['input'];
      output?: never;
      errorText?: never;
      callProviderMetadata?: ProviderMetadata;
    }
  // ... and approval states for tools requiring approval
);
```

